entries.title: Michael Gove set to end misery of leaseholds for millions of homeowners
entries.description: Michael Gove has committed to abolishing the 'outdated, feudal' leasehold system of ownership for almost five million homes by the next general election.

entries.title: Strictly's Helen Skelton caught up in 'brutal' 3am street fight while 'bottles are thrown' in Leeds
entries.description: Strictly's Helen Skelton and her co-stars reportedly had to take cover when they stumbled across a 'shocking' late night  brawl in Leeds city centre on Friday.

entries.title: Crooks will not be able to use slavery or trafficking as reason to remain in UK under new proposal
entries.description: Suella Braverman said that the changes will help prevent false claims of modern slavery and allow officials to focus on genuine victims.

entries.title: Six unanswered questions Tyre Nichols why did police pull him over did they know him cause of death
entries.description: Following the release of disturbing footage showing the violent attack on Tyre Nichols, 28, in Memphis, Tennessee, there are still many questions left unanswered.

entries.title: Cop says he was pressured to resign after writing 'there's no such thing as homosexual marriage'
entries.description: Jacob Kersey, 19, resigned from the department in Port Wentworth, a few miles outside Savannah, after refusing to remove a post on Facebook regarding gay marriage and his faith.

entries.title: Stunning seven-bedroom California home designed by architect Frank Lloyd Wright on sale for $4.25M
entries.description: A home designed by Frank Lloyd Wright is now on the market in California for $4.25 million. The seven bedroom, six bathroom home is located about 120 miles southeast of San Francisco.

entries.title: Sydney writer Natalie Fornasier dies after battle with melanoma
entries.description: Popular Australian writer Natalie Fornasier has died at the age of 28 after battling melanoma.

entries.title: Radical NHS blueprint promises more beds, 800 new ambulances and video 'treatment'
entries.description: The Urgent and Emergency Care plan will help take pressure off the NHS - in time to present to voters ahead of the next general election, due by January 2025.

entries.title: Happy Valley star Sarah Lancashire is slapped with parking ticket in London street
entries.description: The actress, 58, who plays Police Sergeant Catherine Cawood, looked far from pleased as she peeled the ticket off her car in west London, where she had parked on a street during prohibited hours.

entries.title: Clip shows restaurant worker clasping Trump's hand while praying as he begins re-election effort
entries.description: Donald Trump was stopped over the weekend by a restaurant worker who became emotional as she gripped the politician's hand and prayed for the success of his presidential campaign.

entries.title: Vladimir Putin's 'threat to kill Boris Johnson' in run-up to Ukraine war
entries.description: Boris Johnson said the Russian leader had bragged it would 'take only a minute' to kill him with a missile after he warned him to abandon his plans to attack Ukraine.

entries.title: Jeremy Clarkson blames newcomers from London for village standoff over Cotswolds Diddly Squat farm
entries.description: Jeremy Clarkson (pictured) said he is yet to win over some of his Cotswolds neighbours - particularly those who have moved from London - who remain unhappy with Diddly Squat Farm.
